          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1586949781518-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>red chilli[es]</strong> into rounds</p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining lime </strong>into 1 wedge per person</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1586949788099-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1586949788099-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1586949788099-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1586949788099-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1586949788099-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>baked</strong> <strong>sweet potato </strong>in half, lengthways, and fill with the<strong> creamy chickpea curry</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chilli rounds </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>toasted cashew nuts </strong>and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
